The paper deals with the problem of Form Understanding in Noisy Scanned Documents (FoUn), which involves tasks such as text detection, optical character recognition (OCR), spatial layout analysis, and entity labeling/linking. These tasks are typically addressed in the computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories of arXiv CS. Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
